examples.text: Mr. <w>Barnett</w> has been teaching history at the high school for twenty years.
We invited the <w>Barnett</w> family to dinner next Saturday.

senses.sense_definition: A male given name transferred from the surname.

examples.text: <w>Barnett</w> Newman was a prominent figure in abstract expressionism.
Although uncommon, <w>Barnett</w> is a strong name for a baby boy.

senses.sense_definition: A place name used for various locations in the United States, such as a community in Georgia.

examples.text: The small community of <w>Barnett</w> is located in Warren County.
They drove through <w>Barnett</w> on their road trip across the state.
